<item>
            <title>[JDK-8244400] MenuItem may cache the size and did not update it when the screen DPI is changed</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8244400</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>In the test/jdk/javax/swing/GraphicsConfigNotifier/StalePreferredSize.java the next code was added to workaround this bug:&lt;br/&gt;
if (component instanceof JMenuItem) {&lt;br/&gt;
MenuItemLayoutHelper.clearUsedParentClientProperties((JMenuItem)component);&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The MenuItemLayoutHelper.clearUsedParentClientProperties must be called automatically when the DPI was changed.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Similar bug for other components:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8201552&quot;&gt;https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8201552&lt;/a&gt;</description>
